<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Black screen with loading circle after running CCleaner]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8221&amp;p=35846#p35846"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">juniper7 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Oh man, I feel for you.<br />Deep cleaning registry, or system files can be a gamble.<br />I never used Start Fresh, as it seems like a half baked way, deleting all the programs one has installed, but keeping other files.<br /><br />The CC registry cleaner section caused problems for me way back.<br />I was only using CC as normal recycle file cleaner (not the registry cleaner) after that.<br /><br />Then a few months ago, I found out certain versions, somehow got infected with super bad malware. <br />It was in the news. <br />From then on, I uninstalled it, and have been using Microsoft Disk Cleanup.<br />Not as fast, but safer security wise. <br /><br /><br />If you used the registry cleaner section of CCleaner, and if you saved the simple .REG file created <br />in &quot;My Documents&quot; folder, you might be able to get to it in safe mode, and double click it.<br /><br />Even though you hate waiting, and would rather throw lemon grenades, <br />is there any way you can access Windows System Restore in safe mode?<br />Has been a lifesaver for me.<br />If you made a Windows restore point sometime before, <br />it is the full registry backup, and works 75% of time.<br /><br /><br />If you did what I did when first time using CC software, <br />I clicked on every file clean box, and screwed up Windows, I had to reinstall operating system.<br />Hope you don't have to go that far. <br />There might be other ways to file check for crucial system files, but usually need operating disc for that.<br /><br />Waiting to get into safe mode, is less work than reinstalling new operating system with usb memory stick!<br /><br />Good Luck.<br /></div><br /><br /><br />Could not get into safe mode, used USB stick to reinstall Windows. yAY<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10096">NoahNicholsFourm</a> — Sat May 26, 2018 6:37 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[juniper7]]></name></author>
<updated>2018-01-07T08:49:59-07:00</updated>
<published>2018-01-07T08:49:59-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8221&amp;p=35220#p35220</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8221&amp;p=35220#p35220"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Black screen with loading circle after running CCleaner]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8221&amp;p=35220#p35220"><![CDATA[
Oh man, I feel for you.<br />Deep cleaning registry, or system files can be a gamble.<br />I never used Start Fresh, as it seems like a half baked way, deleting all the programs one has installed, but keeping other files.<br /><br />The CC registry cleaner section caused problems for me way back.<br />I was only using CC as normal recycle file cleaner (not the registry cleaner) after that.<br /><br />Then a few months ago, I found out certain versions, somehow got infected with super bad malware. <br />It was in the news. <br />From then on, I uninstalled it, and have been using Microsoft Disk Cleanup.<br />Not as fast, but safer security wise. <br /><br /><br />If you used the registry cleaner section of CCleaner, and if you saved the simple .REG file created <br />in &quot;My Documents&quot; folder, you might be able to get to it in safe mode, and double click it.<br /><br />Even though you hate waiting, and would rather throw lemon grenades, <br />is there any way you can access Windows System Restore in safe mode?<br />Has been a lifesaver for me.<br />If you made a Windows restore point sometime before, <br />it is the full registry backup, and works 75% of time.<br /><br /><br />If you did what I did when first time using CC software, <br />I clicked on every file clean box, and screwed up Windows, I had to reinstall operating system.<br />Hope you don't have to go that far. <br />There might be other ways to file check for crucial system files, but usually need operating disc for that.<br /><br />Waiting to get into safe mode, is less work than reinstalling new operating system with usb memory stick!<br /><br />Good Luck.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sun Jan 07, 2018 8:49 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
